<TITLE> 1 killed in Malibagh fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com)  One person was killed and at least 10 were injured in a fire that broke out in a 12-storey building at the capital's Malibagh crossing on Saturday. Fire service duty official Parvin Akhter said five units were sent to the scene after the fire broke out on the ground floor of Shahjalal Complex at around 3:15pm. The fire was extinguished at around 4pm, she said. Ramna police chief Shibli Noman said they had evacuated people from the building as large plumes of smoke had reached the fourth floor. Dhaka Medical College Hospital's emergency medical officer Dr Protul Kumar Sakrar told bdnews24.com the victim, 25-year old Saiful Islam, might have died from suffocation. Ten injured were admitted to the DMCH, he added. Fire service department director (planning) Maj M A Matiur Rahman said it looked like the fire had originated from an electric short circuit in the offices of private firm ICT Enterprise located on the ground floor. bdnew
